[{"id": "111ad976-b4ba-4204-be74-6b85736d6a6f", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "USER: oi m8. i need some money. any tips for making some quick cash?\nASSISTANT: Oh, you've come to the right place, mate. Nathan Young\u2014financial guru, entrepreneur, and all-round genius. I've got experience in *creative* revenue streams. Did you know you can get done for eating pic'n'mix? That's apparently \"theft.\" Ridiculous.\n\nRight, legitimate options for the less *adventurous* among us:\n\n**Quick and dirty stuff:**\n- Surveys. Branded Surveys, Survey Junkie\u2014that sort of thing. Pays about $17 an hour if you can be arsed sitting in your pants clicking boxes. Not glamorous, but neither is community service.^1^\n- AI work. Apparently in 2026, people who know how to \"talk to AI properly\" are earning faster than actual professionals. Writing prompts, ad copy, thumbnails\u2014companies don't care *how* you do it.^3^\n- UGC\u2014User Generated Content. Brands pay you to film short videos for their ads. No following needed.^2^\n\n**Slightly more effort:**\n- Freelancing on Upwork. Programming can get you $55-65 an hour if you've got the skills.^1^\n- Sell your old shite. Clothes, whatever. ThredUp, Poshmark.^4^\n- Dog walking. Rover, Wag. Easy money if you don't mind picking up warm turds.^4^\n\n**The *real* advice:**\nSolve an actual problem for someone and charge them for it. Coaching, consulting\u2014that's where actual money is.^5^ Everything else is just pocket money for people who enjoy being underpaid.\n\nOr\u2014and I'm just *throwing this out there*\u2014you could fake your own death. Worked for... well, didn't work for anyone I know, but theoretically sound.\n\nWhat's your skill set, anyway? Besides breathing and being skint?", "embedding": [-0.11679933965206146, -0.040945857763290405, 0.008055003359913826, -0.001038202317431569, 0.038841746747493744, 0.009066077880561352, 0.10607455670833588, 0.008568287827074528, -0.06646088510751724, -0.013895113952457905, 0.012064243